description:
The operating conditions for alkylating benzene by 1-dodecene were as follows:



        temperature: 135° C.;
        pressure: 4 MPa;
        HSV=1 h−1 (cm3 (benzene+1-dodecene) feed/cm3 of catalyst/hour);
        Benzene/1-dodecene mole ratio: 5.5.

The experimental conditions were as follows:



        temperature of the two reactors: 135° C.;
        pressure: 4 MPa;
        overall HSV over the two reactors: 1 h−1 (expressed as cm3 of feed (benzene+1-dodecene) /cm3 of catalyst/hour);

The experimental conditions were as follows:



        temperature of the two reactors: 135° C.;
        pressure: 4 MPa;
        overall HSV over the two reactors: 1 h−1 (expressed as cm3 of feed (benzene+1-dodecene) /cm3 of catalyst/hour);
